\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Will this actually achieve your objective?\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Honestly: 
\f1\b partially, with an upgrade path.
\f0\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Day 1 of this change:
\f0\b0  every dealer link goes to a search results page on the dealer's site for the watch's reference number. That's ~85% of the way to "the exact watch" \'97 you land on a tightly filtered list (often 1\'963 results) instead of the homepage. For most reference numbers like 
\f2\fs26 126610LN
\f0\fs24 , the dealer's search returns the exact product as the first hit.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Over time:
\f0\b0  you (or me, in follow-up sessions) fill in 
\f2\fs26 dealer-deep-links.json
\f0\fs24  with exact product URLs for the watches you care most about. Those become 100% perfect direct links. The structure is already there to support unlimited overrides.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Going from "homepage" to "filtered search results page for the right reference" is a real, immediate win that works for all 33 dealers \'d7 all 485 watches without me hand-curating thousands of URLs. The override file is the path to perfection for the watches that matter most to you.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
